      • addColumn

        protected void addColumn(int index,
                         java.lang.String databaseName,
                         java.lang.String visibleName,
                         java.lang.String comment,
                         CcddClassesDataTable.InputType inputType,
                         java.lang.Boolean isRowValueUnique,
                         java.lang.Boolean isColumnRequired,
                         java.lang.Boolean isStructure,
                         java.lang.Boolean isPointer)
        Add the header and database column names, and the tool tip text to the list
        Parameters:
        index - column index
        databaseName - name of the column as used in the database
        visibleName - name of the column as seen by the user; e.g., as table editor column headers
        comment - column description used as the table editor column header tool tip text
        inputType - column input type (InputType)
        isRowValueUnique - true if the each row value in the column must have a unique value
        isColumnRequired - true if the column must have a value when the type is committed to the database
        isStructure - true if the the column applies to structure data types
        isPointer - true if the the column applies to pointer data types

      • isStructure

        protected boolean isStructure()
        Determine if this table type contains all of the default protected columns of the Structure table type
        Returns:
        true if this table type contains all of the protected columns of the Structure table type; i.e., this table type represents a structure table

      • isTelemetryStructure

        protected boolean isTelemetryStructure()
        Determine if this table type contains all of the default protected columns of the Structure table type in addition to a column with the Rate input type
        Returns:
        true if this table type contains all of the protected columns of the Structure table type in addition to a column with the Rate input type; i.e., this table type represents a telemetry structure table

      • isCommand

        protected boolean isCommand()
        Determine if this table type contains all of the default protected columns of the Command table type
        Returns:
        true if this table type contains all of the protected columns of the Command table type (but not those of a Structure table type); i.e., this table type represents a Command table
